PRETORIA - The Independent police investigative directorate (IPID) on Tuesday morning in Pretoria affected the arrest of a police crime intelligence operative. The operative, who has not been named as he is yet to appear in court to face charges, allegedly has links to former acting national police commissioner Kgomotso Phahlane. READ:Â IPID not in disarray: Moerane Commission He allegedly defrauded the crime intelligence fund. The man was sentenced to 10 years after he was arrested for cash-in-transit heist in December 1994, but did not go to jail. He was later found and imprisoned in 2013 and was let out on parole in 2015. At the time of his arrest, the man was working as a crime intelligence operative. eNCA